Know all men by these 1116561115, 11131 we John Castle, of Not- tingham, fisher, Richard Burton‚ of the same, grocer, and Henry Higgin‚ of the same, butcher, are held and firmly bound to Robert Stable, Mayor of the town of Nottingham, to the Burgesses and Community of the same town, in a hundred marks of lawful money, to be paid to the same Robert, the Burgesses and Community, and their successors‚ at the feast of Easter next to come after the date of these presents: which payment well and truly to make, we bind ourselves, and each of us by himself and collectively‚ our heirs and successors, by these presents.

In testimony whereof we have put our seals to this present writing. Given on the tenth day of September, in the seventh year of the reign of King Edward the Fourth.
